ead for the way this raid want. For what I could tell you did everything in your power to tell people what to do and explained why. Sadly unlike most places, when someone doesn't listen it ends out killing everyone.<br><br>The good news is by the 3rd or 4th wipe out I think people figured out where the west camp was. &lt;Shake head&gt; You can see it from the Damn portal.. You can see the corpse, how hard could it be? At times I would be at the camp looking at the portal and would see people running for all around the hill to the camp. Coming for the back of the portal hill has always been my favorite. <br><br>Like Verius I also have a list of people that did stupid things, Everything from Training the Camp, wandering or not listening to the Management team. &lt;Cough&gt;I'm on my own List&lt;Cough&gt; It's sad and pathetic that people have to make lists in the first place.<br><br>I do have an idea to deal with this and have something written out that I've sent to Cassia and Pippi to review it for me. (Because their English is gooder then mine) <br><br>Just some good notes. Even with all the deaths I didn't really see anyone whine or bitch about it publicly, that's good. I found the patience level to be high, everyone sit quieting and waited for their orders and so on. (They didn't follow them but they where quiet when the should have been listening) <br><br>I come because I love being part of something big, I want to see people happy and having fun. I support my friends even if I have nothing to gain and only things to loss. I don't care about the loot, I don't care about the Exp. But I do care about my Friends. So as long as there is room for me and the management team well let me keep coming, I'll be there.<br><br>Stay frosty my Friend all is cool.<br> <p><IMG SRC="http://www.coastnet.com/~drake/sig.gif"><BR><IMG SRC="http://www.coastnet.com/~drake/backstab.gif"><BR>I have been asked many of times what class I am. Well that is easy.<BR><I>"I am <B>Rogue</B>: Adventurer, Explorer, Adrenal junky, Gambler, Scout, Puller, Fame seeker, Gypsy, Rake, Jack-of-all-trades, Assassin, Lock smith, and Story teller but I am not a Thief! Well not always."</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/15/01 1:47:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FEAR RAID CONCERNS I HAVE</span><hr size=1> This is going to be a long way, and will attempt to recap, educate and explain to all about some of what happened. It is not meant as a recrimination, nor as finger pointing, but as a tool to learn how to do better. <br><br>We succeeded in breaking the west wall camp in Fear. <br><br>Ok stop, repeat that sentence to yourself 5 times before reading on. Say it like a mantra, over and over again. <br><br>We succeeded in breaking the west wall camp in Fear. <br><br>I want you to repeat this, and keep it in mind as you read the rest of this post and all others on this subject. Keep in mind that the west wall camp is considered to be one of the hardest level 46-55 encounters in the game. The Sacred Band-led CoG did this camp, without calling in an uber guild to help us. All those who participated should be proud as hell of that achievement. When you read the negatives in this post, keep that positive in mind, because in the end, what we did is important. It is a positive point, and it shows that with tenacity, discipline and courage, we can do amazing things on Council raids. <br><br>And now, as you keep that positive in mind, here's the negative. <br><br>How we did this raid was not good. We took 7 hours to break this place. If done correctly, the west wall camp can be broken in as little as 30 minutes. While I don't pretend that we could do it that quickly (because of the sheer number of different guilds involved), we can do it better. <br><br>Now the root of many of the problems on this raid is me. As a level 40 player, I cannot go into the planes, no matter how much I might desire to. My original intention has been to organize the raid (schedule it, deal with sign ups, appoint management positions, etc.) and then turn it over to my appointed raid commander. However, the one I'd appointed was unable to show (for connectivity problems I later found out). I failed to appoint a raid commander at that point, and as a result people didn't know who to follow, many instructions were left out, and miscommunication among the management body ensued all night. This armchair generaling hurt us up until I left.<br><br>We rushed into the plane, hardly before I'd gotten the groups set. Before I knew it, Zellex had gone into the plane and begun kiting, and I for one was not ready. But I didn't hold us up, and I should have. I didn't have an accurate picture of the strategy Zellex was using to kite/pull/break the camp, so was unable to give folks an idea of how to do their thing. It was only on the 3rd run in that I was clear on how it was being done. This should have been set up and explained beforehand, twice if necessary. That won't happen in the future. <br><br>When Zellex suggested the West wall camp, I should have said no, but I deferred to his judgement on this one. Looking at the number of people we had at the start (about 30), I felt that we should not try to break in that way, but didn't say so, and didn't change the camp to the north wall. Had I nominated a battle commander, they would have probably told me to do a north wall camp as well, but I didn't. <br><br>For all of these things I'm sorry. These led to a lot of the problems that came later on. A successful raid starts with a successful management body, and we weren't, and much of the blame for that must fall on me. For those who fought and died and lost experience on this raid, I apologize. <br><br>Now for the things that I had no control over. <br><br>Evac should have been called by a raid commander, which in the end would be Cassia for this one. No one should evac unless the raid commander shouts &quot;EVAC!&quot; To do so causes others to be killed needlessly. Had I let everyone know to follow Cassia's word on this and no one else's, this might not have happened. But I feel I must stress it again. ONLY the raid commander can call evac, no one else. If the raid leader doesn't call it, you don't do it. I know at one point, some folks evaced out thinking that if there were over 4 mobs you should evac. If no one shouted a definite evac, don't do it. <br><br>Ressurections are NEVER to be refused on ANY Sacred Band-led CoG raid. If ANYONE ever refuses a ressurection because they want to wait on a higher level res, they will not be ressed, and can come and loot their corpse whenever they feel the need. I'll explain why. <br><br>48 people were on this raid. At one point, 30 or so were in the plane trying to break the camp, and about half of them died. So let's say 15 people need resses, and there's only one cleric with his gear and ready to res, a level 52 cleric like Verius. Vaard, a level 57 cleric hasn't been ressed yet. The first person to be ressed doesn't want to be ressed by Verius, he's wants the higher level res that Vaard can do. But Vaard isn't in the planes, but his corpse is. Which means Vaard has to be ressed with the 52nd level res, a 90% res. Now that person who refused the first res, gets Vaard's res, a 97% res. Is it fair that Vaard HAD to take the 90% res just so you could get another 7% exp. back? Is it fair to the other 13 people who need to be ressed in 3 hours or less, who just had to wait an extra 5-10 minutes so you could get your extra 7% res back? <br><br>If your answer to that question is yes, don't come on any SB-led CoG raids again. NO ONE's experience, including mine, or anyone else's is more important than ANYONE else's. You do not have the right to make a raid wait for your 7% of experience. It is rude and insulting and inconsiderate. We had this happen on our last Nagafen raid, and it added an hour to the raid at the end. People complain about these raids taking time, well, that's one reason. In future, we will res you as soon as we can, and the first res you get is the one you take or you don't get another chance. That may sound harsh or rude, but how would you feel if you COULDN'T be ressed because someone took up 2 or 3 minutes of the cleric's time refusing his res? <br><br>Listening to directions HAS to be done. We had a lot of miscommunication in the management body, which carried down to the raiders. BUT, I know I said MANY times after the first groups went in, do NOT turn right at the portal, and still people did. On future raids, our management body will have better communication. Make sure your listening is up to the task. <br><br>Assist, assist, assist! We had major problems with either assist not working, or it being ignored. If you are a melee class and assist isn't working AND there are enchanters there and you aren't sure which mob to hit, you'd better not be hitting any of them. Main assist must make sure that you are targeted and attacking, and you MUST shout out what you are hitting. By the time you hit 46, you should have that lesson driven home many times. <br><br>When in the west camp, STAY in the west camp. Your corpse will be dragged to you, you don't have to go and get it. <br><br>If you haven't been given an explicit title like main assist, raid commander, or loot coordinator, don't use the out of character channels. Don't assume you've been given responsibilities unless the RAID COMMANDER has told you so. I apologize again for not specifiying a raid commander. <br><br>I know that at one point, there were some who refused to zone in with their group when told to, because they didn't want to lose anymore exp. Get over it. Just like the ressing issue above, you're experience isn't worth anymore than the people in your group who DID zone in and are putting their butts on the line. If your group leader or the raid commander says zone, by the gods you do it. Refusal to do so can and will get your thrown off the raid, especially if accompanied by a comment like &quot;I don't want to lose anymore exp.&quot;<br><br>Noticed I haven't attached names to any of this. Pointing out people who train the camp, or who refuse reses only serves to piss people off. The people who screwed up KNOW that they srewed up, and this post is not meant to highlight them and make them feel bad. It's meant to be used by us as a learning tool. We've had a very difficult break in. Learn from it, because it was bound to happen sooner or later. Blaming people and name-calling isn't going to make future raids a success, learning from them will. <br><br>For my own sanity, I'm not going to attempt to be a battle commander on SB-led CoG planes raids until I reach level 47. It isn't fair to the raiders, and it isn't fair to myself. I will organize them, possibly making groups if asked. <br><br>What I would like to see is other alliances/people LIKE the Sacred Band step up and lead CoG Planes raids. I would be perfectly happy if one week Zellex led a plane raid, the next week, the Sacred Band led one, then the 3rd week someone from say Haven of Light or Fellowship of Faydark led a raid, then the 4th week, someone from another alliance or guild run one. Even if you're guild is not doing planes on a regular basis, I'd like to see those smaller guilds with just a few planes ready people step up and lead. Because one day, the Sacred Band will have enough folks that we'll have to do them without the CoG, just to be fair to the people in the alliance. I'd like to have someone to take our place when that does happen. If you want any information on how to go about leading these, drop me an email at haemish@mail.com.<br><br>Despite the length and number of negatives in this post, I think we shold come away from it with 2 positives that outweigh everything else. <br><br>1) We learned a lot about how to do it wrong. Now we know what NOT to do, which can be just as important as what TO do. <br>2) We broke the west wall camp, one of the hardest level 46-55 encounters in the game, without help from an uber guild. That alone should tell you that the CoG can do things like this, given the right set of circumstances and discipline. <br><br>Haemish MacLennan<br>Clan Chieftan<br>The Silver Daggers<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplangstrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>P Langstrump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/15/01 2:38:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.interlog.com/~wings/jane/a_lindgren/lindgren_pics/pippi.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FEAR RAID CONCERNS I HAVE</span><hr size=1> *gives Haemish a wicked pat on the back* well done summary!<br><br>Now stop blaming yourself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>Just to add one more thing:  I know this is the Web and all, and noone on the Web reads, only scans information, bla bla... but PLEASE:  Most of the complaints I see about COG raids 