rt or the Lake Rathe Arena (or Grobb if you can manage it) prior to the raid greatly reduces the downtime, especially on a west camp break in that might entail zoning back in naked with a sword. Casters not binding outside the portal also happened, and just shouldn't. Having to send out druids to reconstitute groups made for a nightmare. <br><br>2) Latecomers and no shows. I had a list of about 30 or so people who signed up for the raid. Of that number, about HALF didn't show up at all, or were 2 or more hours late. If you sign up, either make it or post that you were unable to make it. I know there were some connectivity issues with some folks that night, but post or email the person organizing it beforehand. If you know you'll be late past the cutoff time, post or email the organizer about that so they'll know what to expect. Since we were so short on folks, I allowed late comers all night, 2 full groups worth. This did however create confusion, as they weren't here to hear what mission briefing we had. You need to be on time because it takes time to take attendance, organize groups and brief them on what they are to do. If you come in late, causing regrouping issues, the 1 minute you were late is 1 minute more we're outside the plane, not raiding and having fun. If you're late for RL reasons, that's understandable. If you're late because you have to run from Fironia Vie and didn't do it the previous night or arrange transportation in advance, that's rude not only to the raid organizer and his management body, but to everyone on the raid. <br><br>Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvaardlifeshield.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vaard Lifeshield</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/16/01 12:20:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplySc