ms more than anyone else, it makes people who just reached level 46/47 and are new to the planes feel less appreciated than others (especially if they turn out to be more contributive than someone in their 50s), and (my personal favourite) it puts undue focus on items which in turn often results in single-mindedness (&quot;I am here because of an item, and I deserve it!&quot;), getting-something-out-of-it attitudes, and most of all, even more arguments about what should be included in this point system and what not.  <br><br>Now, ignoring my opinion ... I would like to hear from clerics (and I mean clerics who don't come regularly, i.e., not Vaard/Verius) if they would actually go to fear if such a point system was established.  I know for a fact that even with the system, clerics often don't go to fear after they've gotten specific items in hate, so it may only buy us a little time, nothing more.<br><br>Are there any other methods that would deal with all the above disadvantages? I know it has been mentioned before, why not pay clerics who come to a fear raid? Invite clerics to management?  <br><br>p.s. I know I sound like a broken record, but the Council of Guilds is not an alliance <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><HR><font size=2>Celtic: "Knowing [or Finding] the Oak Tree").... They seem to have frequented oak forests and acted as priests, teachers, and judges. (Encyclopedia Britannica)</font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplangstrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>P Langstrump</A> at: 2/16/01 6:41:05 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> 