span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/16/01 8:07:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/cassia?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FEAR RAID CONCERNS I HAVE</span><hr size=1> Pippi, Haemish, I couldn't agree more.  And Shoji?  Been there, done that.  You're little scenario is no exaggeration at all.  I've lived it.  <br><br>I would love to see Pippi's idea, of finding other ways to entice clerics implimented.  On a side note...<br><br>I think our clerics are rezzing themselves last, meaning that if anyone is going to lose exp, it's them.  I don't like that.  We demand a lot of our clerics in Fear.  They are prime targets, and particularly in a North camp break in, may die many more times than the average Fear raider.<br><br>I would like to see us have our clerics rez others until they only have enough mana for 1 rez (this way mana isn't wasted) and then rez themselves, all of their bodies.<br><br>Just doesn't make any sense to me that after everything else they do, they rez themselves last, risking the corpse getting too old. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/17/01 5:02:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FEAR RAID CONCERNS I HAVE</span><hr size=1> Ok we are beating around the bush here, forget all the other classes the MAIN problem in Fear is Clerics just not showing up. We made a Suggestion for a solution, which was deemed unworthy, So whats your Suggestions for getting Clerics to show up.  I have no problem with Paying with Reagents for Peridots, But I refuse to pay a cleric just to Show up. Heck while your at it Pay me to show up too, its not like I have any regular drops there (I dont count Cube drops)  and I have been to More Fear Raids than Hate.  I think Vaard (and Clerics that show, only name in Mind right now) is completely correct in the fact that why should he be one of the few clerics risking his EXP (no his exp is not more important than others but he is at least putting his on the line like the rest of us that show) in Fear just to Roll against 8 or more Clerics on a Cleric Item in Hate.  I dont Find that Fair At ALL.<br><br>Rangers Show up to Both, Pallys at Both, Enchs Show at Both..... Getting the point here.....whats Wrong with the Clerics in CoG.   Not counting the few that do show.<br><br><br>Lagdalen<br><br><br>Just Speaking my Mind, its Late I am going to Bed now<br><br>PS.  as to Raising the lvl on Meleers for Dragon Raids and what not, should be under Dragon raid topic but was mentioned  here.  Flarren at lvl 44 at time of Vox and Naggy, Didnt get healed at either one, and did not get feared either, at the same time cutting himself some very nice looking Dragon Steaks.  Yes he did Die both Times but he died barely less than 30 second before they did both times.  I can see raising it a few lvls for Melee's Like 42 or 43 but not to the same lvl as casters. Its the Resist gear that makes the difference.<br><br>Dragon Part was added by Flarren <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showMessageRange?topicID=102.topic&start=21&stop=33>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcounci